How to create a custom Santa or Therapist Default

12. December 202112. December 2021 | cindysimblr

Here, I will show you how to create a Default for the Sims 2 Santa Claus or Therapist. This is different from a DR that replaces the clothes – this method replaces the Sim itself. In fact, it uses a similar method you would use for creating a DR for the Pollination Technician or the perfect Plantsim.

Please be careful when working with custom Therapist or Santa Defaults. Do not attempt to use the Therapist or Santa in another way then was attempted by the game (e.g. by adding either of them to the family). Test your DR in a Test-hood before adding it to your main hood to make sure it does not cause corruption.

According to my own testing, it should be save to remove the DR from your downloads folder again – the Santa memory reverts back to the Sims 2 Santa Claus. Still, proceed with caution.

The Santa Template includes Mortia and Laura’s version of Honeywell’s mod that allows CC trees to summon Santa. All credit goes to the original creators!

Required programs:

  • Sims 2 and the Sims 2 Bodyshop
  • Sims 2 Pack Clean Installer
  • SimPe

Tutorial

Download the Santa template and/or the Therapist template.

Create your Sim in Bodyshop. You can create literally any Sim Teen to Elder. Technically, you can create a child, but the animations won’t match. I have not tested toddlers.

Package your Sim. Click package Sim to file. Insert any name and description. The file will be saved to your desktop.

Open the saved file with clean installer.

Click install – a window will pop up.

Make sure the file extension is set to package. You can unclick the default installation button and select and installation folder if you want to. Personally, I just like to create a new folder on the desktop.

Close the clean installer, open your new folder. Inside, there should be a filename made out of a weird string of numbers. For me, it’s the first one in the list, but that’s not always the case. Open this file with SimPe.

Right click in the resource window and click add.

At the right bottom, select DBPF package (or all files) and navigate to your Santa/Therapist template. Click open.

Click on Object Data (OBJD). In the Editor, you can change the filename. Click commit. NEVER change the GUID.

In Catalogue Description, you can change the name as shown in game (and in the Santa memory). Note that Santa Claus MUST have a first and last name.

The last name is what will be shown in the “best friends with Santa” memory (just like Santa is shown, not Claus).

That’s it! Save your file and rename it into something more descriptive than a string of numbers (e.g. DR_therapist). You can now put the Default file in your download folder. If you upload the Default, make sure to include any CC you used for the creation of your Sim (i.e. all the content of the folder you installed with the Clean Installer).

Let me know if anything is unclear.
